==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rant
<hw>Rant</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Ranted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Ranting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OD. <ets>ranten</ets>,
<ets>randen</ets>, to dote, to be enraged.]</ety> <def>To rave in
violent, high-sounding, or extravagant language, without dignity of
thought; to be noisy, boisterous, and bombastic in talk or declamation;
<as>as, a <ex>ranting</ex> preacher</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Look where my <qex>ranting</qex> host of the Garter comes!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rant
<hw>Rant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>High-sounding language, without
importance or dignity of thought; boisterous, empty declamation;
bombast; <as>as, the <ex>rant</ex> of fanatics</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is a stoical <qex>rant</qex>, without any foundation in the
nature of man or reason of things.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ranter</ent>⟦br⟧
